               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-692" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-692" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-692" type="surname" value="COLLIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-692" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN COLLIS.</persName>
                  </hi> I am assistant to Messrs. Bull and Way, of St. Martin's-lane, woolen-drapers. On Wednesday, the 28th of July, the prisoner presented me with this order for kerseymere (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>,) he said he had got it from Mr. Holman—I took it to Mr. Way.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-693" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-693" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-693" type="surname" value="WAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-693" type="given" value="HENRY SAVORY"></interp>HENRY SAVORY WAY.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a woollen-draper, and live at No. 52, St. Martin's-lane—Collis brought me this order—I went to the prisoner and asked if he brought it from Mr. Holman—he said "Yes"—I said, "Did Mr. Holman write it?"—he said, "Yes"—he afterwards said Mrs. Holman gave it him, and afterwards that he found it—I gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-694" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-694" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-694" type="surname" value="HOLMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-694" type="given" value="SIMON"></interp>SIMON HOLMAN.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a tailor, and deal with Mr. Way. I sent no order to him by the prisoner—I have known the prisoner fifteen years—he knew I dealt there—this order is not my writing.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> A butcher asked me to take the order to Mr. Bull; I was not aware that I did wrong.</p>
